                <a name="LETTER.BLOCK22"></a><table style="background-color: rgb(255, 209, 40);" bgcolor="#ffd128" border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK22"><tr><td style="color:#333333;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;text-align: left;" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><br /></td></tr></table><a name="LETTER.BLOCK7"></a><table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK7"><tr><td style="color:#333333;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;text-align: left;" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left">
<p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 14pt; color: rgb(11, 71, 157);" align="center"><b>Treasures or Clutter?&nbsp;</b></p>
<p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(11, 71, 157);" align="center"><b>&nbsp; &nbsp;</b></p>
<p style="font-size: 12pt; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><b></b></p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">It's the end of the school year and that means your kids will be bringing home everything they have made throughout the year. From art work to projects to A+ essays, determining what to keep and what to toss can be tough.</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">Decide how you will collect everything:</p>
<ul><li><strong>You're sentimental:</strong> If you can't bear to part with every doodle and creation your children have made, get a large box for each child put everything in it so you can sort it later. </li><li><strong>You're selective:</strong> If you are less than attached to the project that got a C, just throw it away and put the things you really care about in a box to further sort at a later time.</li></ul>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">Determine what to save:</p>
<ul><li><strong>Younger kids:</strong> If your kids are younger they will probably have more drawings than schoolwork. Save things that are meaningful such as handprints, a special card or a hand-drawn picture of your family.</li><li><strong>Older kids:</strong> Depending on how old they are, your kids might make the decision to throw things out on their own. Make sure you have them go through their work so they can pick out what's meaningful to them. If there still seems to be a lot to sort through, help them to determine what should really be saved.</li></ul>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">Choose how you will save it:</p>
<ul><li><strong>Take a picture:</strong> For trophies, shadowboxes or other large items, taking a picture then throwing it away will help remind you of your kids' accomplishments without adding clutter.</li><li><strong>Get crafty:</strong> Make a scrapbook or time capsule to collect and remember the fun memories and moments from the school year.</li><li><strong>Simply store it:</strong> You can three-hole punch drawings and paintings or get a folder for each of your children to store their favorite art and schoolwork. You can even put them in a box labeled with the year and grade so you can find them easily later. </li></ul>
<span>Clearing out the clutter and determining what is truly a treasure doesn't have to be difficult. Once everything is organized, you'll be able to find everything easily and take a trip down memory lane anytime you'd like.</span><br /><p style="font-size: 8pt; text-align: center; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;" align="center"><a style="color: rgb(12, 71, 157); text-decoration: underline; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Geneva;" href="#Top" shape="rect">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;</p></td></tr></table><a name="LETTER.BLOCK25"></a><table style="background-color: rgb(255, 209, 40);" bgcolor="#ffd128" border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK25"><tr><td style="color:#333333;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;text-align: left;" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(12, 71, 157);">Featured Sitter</span><br /></td></tr></table><a name="LETTER.BLOCK17"></a><table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK17"><tr><td style="color:#333333;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;text-align: left;" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left">
<div style="text-align: left;" align="left">
<p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;" align="center"><span style="color:#0c479d;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:18pt;"><b> Meet Sara!&nbsp;</b></span></p>
<table class="imgCaptionTable" style="text-align: center; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; width: 172px;" width="172" align="left"><tr><td class="imgCaptionImg" style="text-align: center;" width="173" rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td></tr><tr><td class="imgCaptionText" style="text-align: center; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 8pt;" rowspan="1" colspan="1">
<div><span style="color: rgb(12, 71, 157);">Sara with her niece and nephew</span><br /></div>
</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">This issue's featured sitter is Sara Christopher, who has been with Rocket City Sitters since October 2010. Sara started working for Rocket City Sitters when she was a nursing student at UAH because it was a job that worked around her class schedule.</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">After graduating in December 2011, Sara is currently the Clinical Director at Chestmed and she's also a Promotional Model with Allstate Promotions. In her free time, she loves photography, traveling, scrapbooking, movies and the New Orleans Saints.</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">Here's what families are saying about Sara:</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><em>"Sara was fantastic and Ava loved her! Thank you so much!"</em></p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><em> -Lindsay B. of Huntsville, mother of two</em></p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><em>"Sara was absolutely wonderful - we were so glad to have her! Thank you for sending her to us, it was such a help."</em></p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><em> -Annie P. of Huntsville, mother of one</em></p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><em>"We were very impressed with Sara and it would be great to have her again."</em></p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><em>-Philipp W. of Huntsville, father of one</em></p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>
<span>To schedule Sara, or another one of our great sitters, call us at 256-272-1727.</span><br /></div>
